   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 📓 Extreme Events – Exploratory Data Analysis & Trend Modelling"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "8f7fce89-e078-41c2-963c-60f916420e03",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This notebook analyzes historically observed **extreme weather events** in Atlantic Canada,\n",
    "as defined by station-specific 95th percentile thresholds (P95).\n",
    "\n",
    "An extreme event represents a **tail occurrence**, not a regular observation, and is therefore\n",
    "best analyzed in terms of **frequency, temporal behavior, and regime shifts**, rather than\n",
    "continuous magnitude prediction.\n",
    "\n",
    "The objectives of this notebook are to:\n",
    "- characterize the temporal evolution of extreme wind and heavy precipitation events,\n",
    "- evaluate whether extreme event frequency has changed over time,\n",
    "- validate the percentile-based methodology used to define extreme events,\n",
    "- conduct a simple trend-based predictive exploration compatible with an event-only dataset.\n",
    "\n",
    "This analysis is exploratory and supports subsequent Business Intelligence reporting."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f64a9009-a807-4c3b-a4db-c0a9e7ed93ab",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Import libraries"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "a4e0da8f-ff87-413a-851e-8f8260ad21be",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "6aee86fb-052d-4f85-8f33-148d709622ed",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "<class 'pandas.core.frame.DataFrame'>\n",
      "RangeIndex: 60378 entries, 0 to 60377\n",
      "Data columns (total 6 columns):\n",
      " #   Column         Non-Null Count  Dtype         \n",
      "---  ------         --------------  -----         \n",
      " 0   ClimateID      60378 non-null  object        \n",
      " 1   Date/Time      60378 non-null  datetime64[ns]\n",
      " 2   EventType      60378 non-null  object        \n",
      " 3   EventValue     60378 non-null  float64       \n",
      " 4   P95_Threshold  60378 non-null  float64       \n",
      " 5   ExtremeFlag    60378 non-null  int64         \n",
      "dtypes: datetime64[ns](1), float64(2), int64(1), object(2)\n",
      "memory usage: 2.8+ MB\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Load extreme events dataset\n",
    "extreme = pd.read_csv(\n",
    "    \"../Capstone/clean data/Fact_Extreme_Events_All.csv\",\n",
    "    parse_dates=[\"Date/Time\"]\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Basic structure\n",
    "extreme.head()\n",
    "extreme.info()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "869d386e-f085-46a4-95f6-7145ea73fea7",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Dataset Description\n",
    "\n",
    "This dataset contains **event-level records** of extreme weather conditions.\n",
    "Each row represents **one extreme event**, identified using a station-specific\n",
    "95th percentile threshold.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Key variables:\n",
    "- **ClimateID**: Unique weather station identifier  \n",
    "- **Date/Time**: Date on which the extreme event occurred  \n",
    "- **EventType**: Type of extreme event  \n",
    "  - *Extreme Wind*: wind gust speed (km/h)\n",
    "  - *Heavy Precipitation*: daily precipitation (mm)\n",
    "- **EventValue**: Observed magnitude of the event (interpretation depends on EventType)\n",
    "- **P95_Threshold**: Station-specific threshold used to classify the event\n",
    "- **ExtremeFlag**: Binary indicator (1 = extreme event)\n",
    "\n",
    "Importantly, the dataset includes **only extreme events**; non-extreme observations are not present."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "479ccac2-796d-4264-99c9-949d7933ef5d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Data Cleaning and Feature Preparation\n",
    "\n",
    "The dataset has already been curated prior to ingestion and contains only validated extreme events.\n",
    "No record-level filtering is required for this analysis.\n",
    "\n",
    "Preparation steps focus on:\n",
    "- ensuring proper date formatting,\n",
    "- deriving basic temporal attributes to support aggregation and trend analysis."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "9bbcc506-8f25-4c36-b2cf-a47d893f6196",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "extreme[\"Date/Time\"] = pd.to_datetime(extreme[\"Date/Time\"])\n",
    "extreme[\"Year\"] = extreme[\"Date/Time\"].dt.year\n",
    "extreme[\"Month\"] = extreme[\"Date/Time\"].dt.month"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 22,
   "id": "5395593b-3926-417f-be0b-33a025f81d72",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Define analytical cutoff date to avoid partial-year edge effects\n",
    "cutoff_date = pd.Timestamp(\"2025-12-31\")\n",
    "\n",
    "extreme = extreme[extreme[\"Date/Time\"] <= cutoff_date]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ae37a802-083d-48d4-890d-306faa52f4a2",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Temporal Cutoff\n",
    "\n",
    "To avoid edge effects caused by incomplete years at the end of the record, the analysis\n",
    "is restricted to events occurring on or before **December 31, 2025**.\n",
    "\n",
    "This ensures that all years included in the analysis represent full observation periods\n",
    "and prevents artificial declines in event counts due to partial data coverage."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b37bb889-9ecf-4a91-94f9-3fcff11ce6ac",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Summary Statistics\n",
    "\n",
    "This section provides a high-level overview of extreme"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 23,
   "id": "ffe585f4-3d85-4569-956f-e9e6640ea7cd",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "EventType\n",
       "Heavy Precipitation    35006\n",
       "Extreme Wind           24480\n",
       "Name: count, dtype: int64"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 23,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "extreme[\"EventType\"].value_counts()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 24,
   "id": "c8e30717-c324-4670-9dfc-a8f1de061fdf",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "summary_by_type = (\n",
    "    extreme[\"EventType\"]\n",
    "    .value_counts()\n",
    "    .reset_index(name=\"EventCount\")\n",
    "    .rename(columns={\"index\":\"EventType\"})\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "sns.barplot(data=summary_by_type, x=\"EventType\", y=\"EventCount\")\n",
    "plt.title(\"Total Number of Extreme Events by Type\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7e7d6ec6-20e7-4b81-b80b-c00e6a54cdd6",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Heavy precipitation events occur more frequently than extreme wind events,\n",
    "reflecting regional climatic characteristics of Atlantic Canada."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "39e21e01-2400-4345-b7da-d5f8d13649e9",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Temporal Distribution of Extreme Events\n",
    "\n",
    "This section evaluates how extreme event frequency evolves over time,\n",
    "which is the primary analytical focus for an event-based climate dataset."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 25,
   "id": "e8fab9ca-0770-49ca-bae9-7667ac2d76e7",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "events_per_year = (\n",
    "    extreme.groupby(\"Year\")\n",
    "    .size()\n",
    "    .reset_index(name=\"EventCount\")\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "sns.lineplot(data=events_per_year, x=\"Year\", y=\"EventCount\")\n",
    "plt.title(\"Annual Frequency of Extreme Events\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 26,
   "id": "0821939a-a7bd-48e5-a556-a4e39df898f2",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "events_by_year_type = (\n",
    "    extreme.groupby([\"Year\", \"EventType\"])\n",
    "    .size()\n",
    "    .reset_index(name=\"EventCount\")\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "sns.lineplot(\n",
    "    data=events_by_year_type,\n",
    "    x=\"Year\",\n",
    "    y=\"EventCount\",\n",
    "    hue=\"EventType\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "plt.title(\"Annual Extreme Events by Type\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "568361d8-cba6-4c99-b0cb-dde4962b04bb",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Extreme event frequency exhibits substantial interannual variability,\n",
    "with higher counts clearly concentrated in more recent decades."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "970ed4fa-f29b-4663-b593-d47884bfecbf",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Distribution of Event Magnitudes\n",
    "\n",
    "Event magnitudes are examined to provide context rather than serve as\n",
    "the primary object of inference.\n",
    "\n",
    "Since this dataset contains only threshold-exceeding events, magnitude\n",
    "values are expected to cluster just above their station-specific P95 thresholds."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 27,
   "id": "1f6d5a71-06eb-4d36-a510-f40f0631d174",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "sns.histplot(\n",
    "    data=extreme,\n",
    "    x=\"EventValue\",\n",
    "    hue=\"EventType\",\n",
    "    bins=40,\n",
    "    kde=True\n",
    ")\n",
    "plt.title(\"Distribution of Extreme Event Magnitudes\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f51bb2fd-3e2b-415f-b3a2-e4789413df69",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "These distributions confirm that extreme events are heterogeneous but\n",
    "do not support magnitude-based prediction. Therefore, subsequent analysis\n",
    "focuses on **event frequency and timing** rather than raw intensities."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f8cfde67-14e4-40ea-bf69-e3d715db5e0c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Threshold Validation\n",
    "\n",
    "This section validates the percentile-based methodology used to identify extreme events."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 28,
   "id": "836fa15e-f1d9-49c1-8ec0-b5729a2f57b3",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "sns.scatterplot(\n",
    "    data=extreme,\n",
    "    x=\"P95_Threshold\",\n",
    "    y=\"EventValue\",\n",
    "    alpha=0.4\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.title(\"Observed Event Value vs Station-Specific P95 Threshold\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"P95 Threshold (station-specific)\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Observed Event Value\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 29,
   "id": "82e1418c-57ef-4624-b644-4772ca38a5bb",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
