    "extreme[[\"EventValue\", \"P95_Threshold\"]].corr()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f134669b-906c-474c-bb63-ed58fdc584c0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The strong positive relationship confirms that extreme events consistently exceed\n",
    "their local climatological thresholds, supporting the robustness of the P95 approach"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "29c0083f-9c08-4484-a878-ee7c05609a7f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Key Analytical Questions\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Has the frequency of extreme weather events changed over time?\n",
    "2. Are extreme wind and heavy precipitation events following similar temporal trends?\n",
    "3. Do the data suggest a long‑term shift toward more frequent extreme events?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "6cc94fba-28ea-4982-bd09-145b9fa39704",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Key Findings from Exploratory Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Extreme event frequency has increased over time**, particularly after the early 2000s.\n",
    "2. **Heavy precipitation events dominate** the extreme event record, though both event types show upward trends.\n",
    "3. **Interannual variability remains high**, but recent years exhibit consistently elevated event counts.\n",
    "4. The **percentile-based definition of extreme events is robust**, providing a location-aware and defensible identification method."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "6a1fb7a8-d679-44be-b7d8-a697263bee5f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Predictive Trend Exploration\n",
    "\n",
    "Given the event-only nature of the dataset, predictive modeling is limited to\n",
    "trend exploration rather than event forecasting.\n",
    "\n",
    "A simple linear regression is used to assess whether the annual count of extreme events\n",
    "exhibits a systematic temporal trend."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 30,
   "id": "68bc343e-3cda-4d91-a761-2b51a1d97624",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "0.8980897779282105"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 30,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import r2_score\n",
    "\n",
    "X = events_per_year[[\"Year\"]]\n",
    "y = events_per_year[\"EventCount\"]\n",
    "\n",
    "model = LinearRegression()\n",
    "model.fit(X, y)\n",
    "\n",
    "events_per_year[\"Fitted\"] = model.predict(X)\n",
    "\n",
    "r2 = r2_score(y, events_per_year[\"Fitted\"])\n",
    "r2"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 31,
   "id": "93ce8a0b-8802-4805-a828-29d5898f7a8f",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "sns.lineplot(data=events_per_year, x=\"Year\", y=\"EventCount\", label=\"Observed\")\n",
    "sns.lineplot(data=events_per_year, x=\"Year\", y=\"Fitted\", label=\"Trend\")\n",
    "plt.title(\"Observed vs Trend-Fitted Extreme Event Frequency\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "be960b7e-5f10-45b3-88f8-bf5037386e88",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The model identifies a positive long-term trend in extreme event frequency.\n",
    "The modest R² reflects inherent climate variability and is expected for\n",
    "event-based environmental data."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ae9b2aab-654f-4ca7-9ca1-623054e11e3d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Assumptions and Limitations\n",
    "\n",
    "- The dataset includes only extreme events; non‑extreme observations are not available.\n",
    "- Early historical records may underrepresent true event frequency due to reporting limitations.\n",
    "- Extreme events are identified using station‑specific percentile thresholds rather than absolute physical limits.\n",
    "- The predictive exploration is trend‑based and does not imply causality or operational forecasting.\n",
    "- Spatial dependence between stations is not explicitly modeled in this analysis."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "8078222c-10af-4201-9f79-952ecd2c9042",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Conclusion and Next Steps\n",
    "\n",
    "This analysis documents a clear increase in the frequency of extreme weather events\n",
    "in Atlantic Canada, consistent with a shift toward more persistent climatic extremes.\n",
    "\n",
    "These findings support further integration with sustained wetness indicators\n",
    "and downstream Business Intelligence dashboards to explore compound climate risk."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 32,
   "id": "4a6d8ca8-4b9e-49bf-9902-13eb02c99289",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "events_per_year.to_csv(\"ExtremeEvents_Per_Year.csv\", index=False)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 33,
   "id": "3f5895e2-5616-4d2d-bc56-9f6b7ce09c4c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "events_per_year[[\"Year\", \"EventCount\", \"Fitted\"]].to_csv(\n",
    "    \"ExtremeEvents_TrendModel.csv\", index=False\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
